            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x1E53A855<!--String: "In Bellacorde, the Capp family has a <i>colorful</i> history with the Montys. They utterly hate each other, they've been fighting for generations."--></T>
                  <T>0x39CA7DD1<!--String: "The Capps. The formidable and oldest family of Bellacorde. But not without enemies. Someone keeps defacing their statue in the central plaza of the neighborhood, I'm sure they don't like that."--></T>
                  <T>0x97A0F051<!--String: "The Capps are everywhere in Bellacorde, even after their death. Sometimes you can see old Consort Capp floating around the neighborhood. It's really annoying."--></T>
                  <T>0xB6A23E8B<!--String: "The Capps from Bellacorde have one of the oldest ancestries around, I think they were even related with the Thebes somehow. A very <i>intricate</i> family."--></T>
                  <T>0x17F296DE<!--String: "The neighborhood of Bellacorde and its oldest family, the Capps, are one and the same. Romance, chivalry, elegance...and drama. <i>A LOT</i> of drama."--></T>
                  <T>0xB506E1E9<!--String: "There's <i>a lot</i> of noble families in Bellacorde. No wonder everyone is obsessed with luxury over there."--></T>
                </L>
